body:
# Assistants

The Assistants API builds persistent AI assistants that manage conversation state, use tools, and process files. Unlike direct [[openai/chat]] completions, assistants handle multi-turn context automatically.

## Create an Assistant

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI(); // reads OPENAI_API_KEY from env

const assistant = await client.beta.assistants.create({
  name: "Data Analyst",
  model: "gpt-4o",
  instructions: "You are a data analyst. Analyze data, create visualizations, and explain insights clearly.",
  tools: [
    { type: "code_interpreter" },
    { type: "file_search" },
  ],
});

console.log(`Assistant ID: ${assistant.id}`);
```

## Threads and Messages

Threads hold conversation history. Messages are added to threads, then a run executes the assistant against the thread:

```javascript
// Create a thread
const thread = await client.beta.threads.create();

// Add a user message
await client.beta.threads.messages.create(thread.id, {
  role: "user",
  content: "Analyze the sales data and identify the top 3 trends.",
});

// Create a run
const run = await client.beta.threads.runs.create(thread.id, {
  assistant_id: assistant.id,
});

console.log(`Thread: ${thread.id}, Run: ${run.id}`);
```

## Runs

Runs execute the assistant against a thread. Poll for completion or use streaming:

```javascript
// Poll for completion
let runStatus = await client.beta.threads.runs.retrieve(thread.id, run.id);

while (runStatus.status !== "completed") {
  await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));
  runStatus = await client.beta.threads.runs.retrieve(thread.id, run.id);

  if (runStatus.status === "requires_action") {
    // Handle tool calls — see [[openai/function-calling]]
    const toolCalls = runStatus.required_action.submit_tool_outputs.tool_calls;
    // ... process tool calls and submit outputs
  }

  if (runStatus.status === "failed") {
    throw new Error(`Run failed: ${runStatus.last_error?.message}`);
  }
}

// Get the assistant's response
const messages = await client.beta.threads.messages.list(thread.id);
const response = messages.data[0].content[0].text.value;
console.log(response);
```

### Streaming Runs

```javascript
const stream = client.beta.threads.runs.stream(thread.id, {
  assistant_id: assistant.id,
});

for await (const event of stream) {
  if (event.event === "thread.message.delta") {
    const content = event.data.delta.content?.[0]?.text?.value || "";
    process.stdout.write(content);
  }
}
```

## Tools

Assistants support three tool types:

### Code Interpreter

Executes Python code in a sandboxed environment. Can process files, perform calculations, create charts, and run data analysis:

```javascript
tools: [{ type: "code_interpreter" }]
```

### File Search

Search over uploaded documents using RAG. Supports PDF, TXT, MD, DOCX, and more:

```javascript
// Create a vector store and upload files
const vectorStore = await client.beta.vectorStores.create({ name: "Knowledge Base" });
await client.beta.vectorStores.files.create(vectorStore.id, { file_id: uploadedFile.id });

// Attach to assistant
tools: [{ type: "file_search" }],
tool_resources: { file_search: { vector_store_ids: [vectorStore.id] } }
```

### Function Calling

Define custom tools the assistant can invoke. See [[openai/function-calling]] for the full pattern:

```javascript
tools: [{
  type: "function",
  function: {
    name: "get_weather",
    description: "Get current weather for a location",
    parameters: {
      type: "object",
      properties: {
        location: { type: "string", description: "City name" },
      },
      required: ["location"],
    },
  },
}]
```

## Lifecycle

| Resource | Persistence | Scope |
|----------|-------------|-------|
| Assistant | Permanent until deleted | Organization-wide |
| Thread | Permanent until deleted | Per conversation |
| Message | Permanent within thread | Per thread |
| Run | One-time execution | Per thread |
| Vector Store | Permanent until deleted | Shareable across assistants |
